e versions are inherited correctly from the parent POM.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Java dependencies**\\n\\nJava compilation doesn’t differentiate between direct and transitive dependencies as long as everything is on the classpath. However, \\\"normal use\\\" could demand jackson-annotations to annotate test classes, which I believe comes transitive via jackson-databind. So, do I need to include com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind again? It’s already included through the generator. I might need to set up \\\"testImplementation com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:4.38.0\\\" to cover everything adequately for testing purposes.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The Jackson module is an add-on for victools jsonschema-generator; its POM marks the core generator and Jackson artifacts as provided, so a generated test that only depends on jsonschema-module-jackson is unlikely to reach meaningful usage or may fail compilation when following documented examples.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:4.38.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Documented usage creates a SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder and SchemaGenerator, and the module POM declares jsonschema-generator as a provided dependency rather than a transitive runtime dependency. Adding the matching aligned version supplies the core API and its Jackson/ClassMate transitive dependencies needed to exercise JacksonModule.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears necessary. Meaningful tests should instantiate JacksonModule with SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder/SchemaGenerator and use small model classes annotated with Jackson annotations such as @JsonProperty, @JsonIgnore, @JsonPropertyDescription, @JsonSubTypes, or @JsonTypeInfo, then assert the generated schema reflects those annotations.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the scaffold already injects provided dependencies from the target POM, the extra generator dependency may be redundant, but it matches the library's documented normal use and aligned-version recommendation.\",\n    \"Coverage can be superficial if tests only instantiate JacksonModule without driving schema generation over annotated classes.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0478dadea38a8d26016a3f1c8bcf208197a5813fcacb953d55\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2033, "output": 852, "cacheRead": 11776, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 14661, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782520961104, "responseId": "resp_0478dadea38a8d26016a3f1c816e7081978ae72e5006c3b8fc"}, "toolResults": []}
